 round slices (2 mm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"30 g sesame oil"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 g honey"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"140 g light soy sauce"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 pinch dried chilli flakes              (optional)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"4 cod fillets (approx. 125 g each)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g tinned baby corn, drained, halved lengthways"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g sugar snap peas"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1000 g water"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp fine sea salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"250 g basmati rice"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","2682 kJ \/ 634 kcal","39.8 g","94.5 g","9 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["Getting kids to enjoy fish dishes can sometimes be tricky, but we think they’ll love the sweet honey and soy marinade on these cod fillets. Using the Varoma to steam the cod and vegetables together in paper parcels, while cooking the rice below, keeps the fish tender. Serve the parcels unopened - children will love unwrapping them to see what’s inside!","Substitute cod with any white fish (e.g. pollock, haddock or hake)."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","55m","4 portions"]}